.TH ABRAFLEXI-MCP-TEST 1 "February 2026" "1.0.1" "AbraFlexi MCP Server Manual"
.SH NAME
abraflexi-mcp-test \- test MCP tool registration and AbraFlexi connectivity
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B abraflexi-mcp-test
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B abraflexi-mcp-test
runs a suite of checks against the AbraFlexi MCP server:
.IP \(bu 2
Verifies that all expected MCP tools are registered with valid signatures.
.IP \(bu 2
Tests connectivity to the configured AbraFlexi instance.
.IP \(bu 2
Optionally tests write operations (when read-only mode is disabled).
.PP
This is useful for validating the installation and configuration before
putting the server into production.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B ABRAFLEXI_URL
URL of the AbraFlexi server (required).
.TP
.B ABRAFLEXI_COMPANY
Company identifier in AbraFlexi (required).
.TP
.B ABRAFLEXI_LOGIN
Username for authentication (required).
.TP
.B ABRAFLEXI_PASSWORD
Password for authentication (required).
.TP
.B READ_ONLY
When set to \fBtrue\fR (default), write-operation tests are skipped.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
All tests passed.
.TP
.B 1
One or more tests failed.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR abraflexi-mcp (1),
.BR abraflexi-mcp-start (1)
